# TFPT — project map & contribution workflow

TFPT is a discrete "compiler": two axioms — seam constant `c3 = 1/(8π)` (P1) and
carrier rank `g_car = 5` (P2) — build `D5 ⊕ A3 + μ4 ⇒ E8` and read off the SM,
constants and scale grammar. Every load-bearing claim must be machine-checked.

## Where things live

- **Active papers (root, 9 docs)** — compiled by `build.sh notes` (which also builds
  `changelog.tex` as a tenth standalone deliverable):
  `introduction.tex`, `tfpt_1_architecture_e8.tex`, `tfpt_2_standard_model.tex`,
  `tfpt_3_e8_audit_bootstrap.tex`, `tfpt_4_frontier.tex`, `tfpt_5_redteam.tex` (the
  adversarial audit: Targets A–E, what survives, what each reduces to, the kill tests),
  `tfpt_horizon_readouts.tex`, `tfpt_research_contracts.tex`, `origin_theory.tex` (the
  "Origin Theory" synthesis: seam=horizon keystones, order-30 Coxeter cycle, gapped unique
  attractor; `[I]/[L]` core `v53`–`v56` + one `[P]` cyclic interpretation, kept strictly apart).
- **Shared TeX fragments (single sources — never fork them; all live in `tex-artefacts/`
  and are `\input` by documents compiled from the repo root, so the paths read
  `tex-artefacts/<name>`):**
  `tex-artefacts/tfpt_style.tex` — colours, status markers, the `\veri` macro, the tcolorbox
  families and the running header/footer (it in turn `\input`s `tex-artefacts/tfpt_figures.tex`,
  the shared TikZ figure macros: claim stack, anchor cockpit, E8 glue, 2/3 motif, K5).
  `tex-artefacts/tfpt_docset.tex` — THE canonical document-set box; any change to the document
  list happens ONLY here.
  `tex-artefacts/tfpt_status.tex` — THE canonical "status at a glance" card.
  `tex-artefacts/verification.tex` — THE master script→check index table (every registered
  `vN_*.py` listed exactly once). **GENERATED — never edit by hand.** Single source:
  `verification/script_registry.csv` (column `what_tex`); regenerate with
  `bash build.sh gen` (or `python3 verification/make_script_index.py`), which also
  regenerates `website/components/ScriptIndex.tsx` from the same registry.
  `changelog.tex` (kept at the repo root, NOT in `tex-artefacts/`, because it is also a
  standalone `build.sh notes` deliverable) — THE canonical dated changelog; dual-mode
  (compiles standalone AND is imported at the end of `introduction.tex` via
  `\def\ChangelogImported{1}\input{changelog}`). **Every committed change** (new `vN`
  module, status change, paper/website edit, infrastructure) **adds a dated entry to
  `changelog.tex` in the same change** — newest first, plain LaTeX only (no
  doc-specific macros).
- **Verification suite** — `verification/`: `vN_*.py` (numbered claims), `run_all.py`
  (runner), `tfpt_constants.py` (shared primitives + `check()` harness),
  `status_ledger.csv` (**source of truth**), `freeze_file.csv` (kill criteria),
  `make_manifest.py`, `make_figures.py`, `README.md`, `wolfram/` (independent path).
- **Sync infrastructure** (all in `verification/`, stdlib-only python3):
  `script_registry.csv` + `script_clusters.csv` — THE single source for the script
  index (one row per `vN`: cluster, `what_web`, `what_tex`); `make_script_index.py` —
  generates `tex-artefacts/verification.tex` + `website/components/ScriptIndex.tsx`;
  `make_docs_map.py` — generates `docs_map.csv` (paper → section → scripts cited →
  last-changed date, WITHOUT splitting the papers) + `website_map.csv` (website file →
  scripts/docs mentioned) + the committed date sidecar `docs_map_dates.json`;
  `audit_sync.py` — THE one sync audit (see the `sync-maps` rule); `audit_baseline.json` —
  frozen exceptions (entries may only be REMOVED, never added for new work).
- **Figures** — `figures/*.pdf` (regenerated by `make_figures.py`; includes
  `coxeter_circle.pdf` and `attractor.pdf` used by `origin_theory.tex`).
- **Lean** — `experiments/lean4-carrier-rigidity/` (repo) = `lean4-carrier-rigidity/` (shipped).
- **Content identity** — `manifest.sha256` (TeX/figures/verification + wolfram),
  `lean_manifest.sha256` (Lean archive). NOT the Overleaf zip hash. `make_manifest.py`
  keeps explicit `TEX`/`FIG` lists (add new active docs/figures there, e.g.
  `origin_theory.tex`, `figures/coxeter_circle.pdf`, `figures/attractor.pdf`); the Lean
  manifest records the **canonical shipped path** `lean4-carrier-rigidity/` (via
  `SHIP_LEAN`) while reading from the repo path `experiments/lean4-carrier-rigidity/`.
- **Legacy / sources** — `_archive/` (`tfpt-45/` 7 original papers +
  `source_extracts/`, `paper-latex/` old versions, `paper-pdf/`, root `notebooks/`).
  Read for context; do not treat as active unless asked. (The old `tfpt-breakthrough`
  note was deleted; its scale-grammar / action-ladder `1:5:10` / `g_car=5`
  overdetermination content lives in `tfpt_1`.)
- **Python venv** — `experiments/tfpt-discovery/.venv` (mpmath, numpy, sympy, scipy).
- **Website** — `website/` (Next.js, static, Vercel): a public mirror of the 8 docs +
  the verification suite, driven by `lib/papers.ts`, `lib/predictions.ts`, `lib/glossary.ts`,
  `lib/release.ts`, `public/papers/*.pdf`, `public/verification/*.py`, and the
  `/verification` interactive DAG + in-browser (Pyodide) script reproducer. It must be
  updated in the same change as the theory/scripts — see the **`website-sync` rule** for the
  file-by-file mapping.

## Status markers (use everywhere; never silently upgrade)

Two layers, kept in sync:
- **Documents (display)** show a simplified FOUR-class marker via the `tex-artefacts/tfpt_style.tex`
  macros `\mE \mC \mO \mX`: `[E]` exact/machine-proven (identity, Lie/lattice, formalised, numerical FP)
  · `[C]` conditional (physical/bridge/readout, under named hypotheses) · `[O]` open/axiom · `[X]`
  falsifiable kill test. The legacy fine-grained macros (`\tI \tL \tF \tN \tIalg \tInum \tP \tB \tR \tA
  \tX`) still exist as aliases that render their class, but new text should use `\mE/\mC/\mO/\mX`.
- **Ledger (source of truth)** keeps the FINE per-claim type in `status_ledger.csv`
  (Axiom / Formal / Lattice / Numerical / Identity / Physical) — no fidelity is lost.
Open gates stay `[O]`/`[C]`; see the residual-gates table in `verification/README.md`
and the `GATE.*` rows in the ledger.

## Workflow for a NEW finding (follow in order)

1. **Explore** computationally first (throwaway shell snippet) to confirm the number/identity.
2. **Write `verification/vN_<name>.py`** — derive from `{c3, g_car}` (import from
   `tfpt_constants`), use `check()/summary()/reset()`, exact `sympy` where possible.
   Mark honest scope in the docstring. Never fabricate a result to force a pass.
3. **Register** it in `run_all.py` (`MODULES` list) and run the file standalone.
4. **Integrate into the affected section.** This is mandatory, not optional — a
   finding that is not in the papers does not exist, and **content produced from a
   script must be cited with `\veri{vN_<name>.py}` in the *exact* section/box where
   that content lives** (not merely "somewhere in the paper"). For every new script:
   - add the theorem/keybox/table-row carrying the result, with the correct status
     marker and an inline `\veri{vN_<name>.py}` reference, **in the affected
     section** of the paper whose narrative it belongs to (a script may be cited in
     several sections if it feeds several). `audit_sync.py` enforces this: a script
     cited only in the master index table FAILS the audit;
   - add one row to **`verification/script_registry.csv`** (cluster + `what_tex` +
     `what_web`) and run `bash build.sh gen` — this regenerates the master index
     table AND the website `ScriptIndex.tsx` (never edit those two by hand);
   - if the finding changes a status, update the **status card** in
     `introduction.tex` (the `Rest = (U_wall) ⊕ (G_metric) ⊕ (F_frontier)` keybox)
     **and** the status source in `tfpt_4_frontier.tex` (frontier/QG) so markers
     never disagree across docs.
5. **Mirror in Wolfram (the independent second path) — mandatory for exact results.**
   If the finding is an **exact algebraic / identity / lattice / Pascal** result,
   add the matching `checkExact[...]`/`check[...]` to
   `verification/wolfram/tfpt_readouts.wl`, run it (`wolframscript -file
   tfpt_readouts.wl`), and update **both** the count in `verification/wolfram/README.md`
   and the `GATE.WOLFRAM.01` row in the ledger to the new `N/N` total. Numerical
   ODE/PDE/scipy-only results (e.g. monodromy solves, unitarisation) stay Python-only —
   say so explicitly in the `.wl` comment and the README table. The Wolfram `.wl`,
   its README count, and the ledger count must always agree.
6. **Ledger**: add/update a row in `status_ledger.csv` (7 cols:
   `claim,statement,type,location,depends_on,script,external`). Quote fields with commas.
6b. **Changelog**: add a dated entry to `changelog.tex` (newest first) describing the
   finding/change in the same change, **mentioning the new `vN` module id** (enforced
   by `audit_sync.py` for every non-grandfathered script). The changelog is part of
   `build.sh notes` and is imported at the end of `introduction.tex` — it must always
   compile in both modes.
7. **Recompile + sync + audit** — run the pipeline:
   `bash build.sh release` (= gen → compile all docs → website mirror sync →
   `audit_sync.py` → `npm run build`). It fails on any overfull > 30pt, missing
   citation, stale generated file, changelog gap or website drift.
8. **DAG node** (only if the script backs a node): add its filename to the node's
   `scripts` in `website/components/VerificationDag.tsx`; reflect any status change in
   the website cards (`StatusPyramid.tsx`, `orientation/StatusMatrix.tsx`).
9. **Browser-check** the touched website page(s) — see the `website-sync` rule.
10. **Refresh manifests** (always last): `python verification/make_manifest.py`.

## Maintenance commands (run from `verification/` with venv active)

```bash
. ../experiments/tfpt-discovery/.venv/bin/activate
python run_all.py                         # must end "ALL CHECKS PASSED"
wolframscript -file wolfram/tfpt_readouts.wl   # independent path; must end "ALL WOLFRAM CHECKS PASSED"
python make_figures.py                    # only if a figure's data changed
python make_manifest.py                   # regenerate manifest.sha256 + lean_manifest.sha256 (do LAST)
```

**THE sync audit** (replaces the old loose shell snippets; from repo root):

```bash
bash build.sh audit        # = python3 verification/audit_sync.py; must end "AUDIT OK"
```

It checks, in both directions: suite files ↔ `run_all.py` ↔ `script_registry.csv` ↔
ledger; generated surfaces fresh (`verification.tex`, `ScriptIndex.tsx`, content maps);
every script `\veri`-cited in a paper BODY (master index alone does not count) and every
`\veri`/`\vref` target registered; every non-grandfathered module id in `changelog.tex`;
website mirror byte-identical (PDFs + `vN` scripts + `release.ts` hashes + versions);
wolfram README/ledger counts; overfull boxes. Exceptions: `audit_baseline.json` (frozen).

Wolfram **live** run (the audit only compares the recorded counts; actually executing
the `.wl` still requires wolframscript):

```bash
wolframscript -file wolfram/tfpt_readouts.wl   # must end "ALL WOLFRAM CHECKS PASSED"
```

Full pre-commit pipeline (from repo root):

```bash
bash build.sh release      # gen -> compile 10 docs -> website sync -> audit -> npm build
```

## Deep-sync rules (updates must be COMPLETE, never superficial)

A change is **not done** when one box or one file mentions it — it is done when **every
surface that states the affected fact agrees**. Concretely:

- **Trace every affected statement.** When a result upgrades/supersedes an earlier claim,
  FIRST consult the generated content maps to enumerate the surfaces (see the
  `sync-maps` rule): `grep <vN_script> verification/docs_map.csv verification/website_map.csv`
  lists every paper section and website file that carries the affected content. THEN
  grep ALL active docs + website for the superseded wording, e.g.:
  `grep -rn "single remaining\|one missing\|genuine remaining\|stays open" *.tex website/lib website/components`
  Every hit that the new result touches must be rewritten (or explicitly marked with a
  dated "status update" note) — leaving a stale "X is the remaining input" sentence
  anywhere is a defect, not a style issue.
- **Status surfaces move together** (one finding ⇒ all of these in the SAME change):
  the affected paper section(s) with `\veri{}`, the intro script index, the intro status
  card + "sharper aliases" prose, `tfpt_4_frontier` status, `tfpt_research_contracts`
  (if a gate/residual moved), `origin_theory` (if the gap list moved), `next.txt`,
  `changelog.tex`, the ledger, and the website (`ScriptIndex.tsx`, `VerificationDag.tsx`,
  `papers.ts` abstract+sections of the affected paper, `StatusPyramid.tsx` /
  `orientation/StatusMatrix.tsx` on status changes, `predictions.ts` on prediction changes).
- **`papers.ts` mirrors paper content, not just titles.** When a paper gains/loses a
  section or a section's claim changes status, the corresponding `sections` entry in
  `website/lib/papers.ts` must be updated in the same change.
- **No old-version framing.** The active docs and website never compare against or cite
  "TFPT 4.5", "Papers 1–7", `tfpt-45` or per-old-paper attributions ("Paper 3 shows…").
  Results are attributed to the current documents/axioms/scripts. (The only exception:
  `tfpt_3`'s cascade *bridge*, which is a theorem about the old cascade as an object.)
- **Single sources stay single.** Document list ⇒ `tfpt_docset.tex` only; changelog ⇒
  `changelog.tex` only; status ⇒ ledger only. Never re-type these per document.
- **Papers are English.** All paper/website prose is English (`next.txt` is the only
  German-allowed file). Check any new text before committing.
- **Visual sanity is part of the update.** After substantive TeX edits, check the page
  output (render a few pages) for: boxes breaking badly across pages, tables that cannot
  break (`tabularx` > ~35 rows ⇒ use `xltabular`), unreadable figures, orphaned section
  heads. `grep "Overfull \\vbox" <doc>.log` must be empty.
- **Browser-check website changes.** Any touched website page is verified in the browser
  (not only `npm run build`).

## Invariants (do not break)

- The suite must stay green (`run_all.py` exits 0). Add `vN` checks, never delete.
- **Papers stay in sync with the suite + ledger.** Every script in `run_all.py` is
  cited (`\veri{...}`) in a paper BODY and registered in `script_registry.csv`
  (which generates the master index); every `Open`/`GATE.*` ledger row is reflected
  in a status card with a marker that agrees across all docs. `bash build.sh audit`
  must end "AUDIT OK", and `bash build.sh notes` must report `10 ok, 0 failed`,
  before any commit/manifest refresh.
- **Generated files are never edited by hand**: `tex-artefacts/verification.tex`,
  `website/components/ScriptIndex.tsx`, `website/lib/version.ts`,
  `verification/docs_map.csv`, `verification/website_map.csv`,
  `verification/docs_map_dates.json`. Edit the sources (`script_registry.csv`,
  `script_clusters.csv`, `tex-artefacts/version.tex`, the papers) and re-run
  `bash build.sh gen` / `bash build.sh website`.
- Status markers (display `[E]/[C]/[O]/[X]`; ledger fine types) are never silently upgraded; a downgrade or
  upgrade in one doc must be propagated to the intro status card and `tfpt_4_frontier`
  **and** to the website (`VerificationDag.tsx`, `StatusPyramid.tsx`, `orientation/StatusMatrix.tsx`).
- **The website mirrors the suite + ledger.** `bash build.sh website` copies every
  `vN_*.py` + every active PDF into `website/public/`, stamps `lib/version.ts` and
  refreshes the `lib/release.ts` hashes + version/date; `ScriptIndex.tsx` is generated
  from the registry; `website` builds clean (`npm run build`). All of this is enforced
  by `audit_sync.py`. See the `website-sync` rule.
- `\phiz` already carries a superscript → write `(\phiz)^n`, never `\phiz^n`.
- Reduced Planck mass macro differs per doc (`\Mbar` in most, `\Mpl` in
  `tfpt_4_frontier`) — check the local `\newcommand` before using it.
- After ledger/script/figure/TeX changes, **re-run `make_manifest.py`**; the digest
  is expected to change and should be recorded in any version note.
- **Wolfram is a first-class mirror, not an afterthought.** Every exact
  algebraic/identity/lattice result added to the Python suite must also be added to
  `verification/wolfram/tfpt_readouts.wl` (step 5), and the `.wl` pass-count, the
  `verification/wolfram/README.md` count, and the `GATE.WOLFRAM.01` ledger count must
  always be equal. Numerical-only (scipy ODE/PDE) results are exempt but must be
  flagged as Python-only in both the `.wl` comments and the README table.
- **`changelog.tex` never falls behind.** Every commit that changes theory, suite, papers
  or website carries its dated changelog entry; the changelog compiles standalone AND
  imported (it is part of `build.sh notes`).
- Only write summary `.md` files when explicitly asked.
